                    <note type="abstract" xml:lang="en" corresp="http://syriaca.org/persons http://syriaca.org/johnofephesus/persons">
                        <quote source="#bib1196-7">Damian was of Syrian origin and lived as a monastic ascetic in Egypt before he was made successor to the miaphysite patriarch Peter of Alexandria. He considered patriarch Paul of Antioch as illegitimate and eventually managed to ordain Peter of Callinicum as counter-patriarch in Antioch. Joh. Eph., EH 4.43, is very critical of Damian because of these actions.</quote>
                    </note>
                    <note xml:lang="en" type="abstract" xml:id="abstract-en-1196">In hagiography: Damian was patriarch
            of <placeName ref="http://syriaca.org/place/572">Alexandria</placeName>. He sent a letter
            to <persName ref="http://syriaca.org/person/69">Jacob Baradaeus</persName> hoping for
          communion between the churches. He visited <placeName ref="http://syriaca.org/place/10">Antioch</placeName> but broke from the Patriarch of Antioch, <persName ref="http://syriaca.org/person/75">Peter of Callinicus</persName>, because of the
          Tritheist controversy. This schism ended with the patriarchate of <persName ref="http://syriaca.org/person/88">Athanasius I Gamolo</persName>.</note>
